description: From Latin obumbratus, past participle of obumbrare (“to overshadow, cloud”); ob + umbrare (“to shade”).

entries.meaning: Lying under some projecting part, like the abdomen of certain spiders.

verbs.description: obumbrate (third-person singular simple present obumbrates, present participle obumbrating, simple past and past participle obumbrated)

entries.meaning: To shade; to darken; to cloud.
